response: The media market has huge potential that is yet to be unlocked, even with rapid growth. Internet penetration in many countries is still behind other G20 peers. As of July 2016, the UK had 92% penetration, Japan had 91.1%, the US had 88.5%, Canada had 88.5%, and Germany had 88%.
